---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { CTA } from '../consts';

// SPEAKING. Voice: Full LinkedIn Laura. Talks are real (Cincy AI Week featured
// speaker; Eastern Illinois University guest lecture; Atlanta audit talk).
---
<PageLayout
  title="Speaking"
  description="Laura Seelinger speaks on AI visibility, GEO, and AEO — practical, no-fluff talks and workshops for marketing teams, agencies, and events."
>
  <p class="subhead">talks &amp; workshops</p>
  <p class="prose">
    Giving people something they can actually action — not theory they nod at and
    forget by the parking lot — is the thing that lights me up. My pet peeve is
    leaving a session fired up with no real plan, so I don't do that to a room. I
    speak on AI visibility, GEO, and AEO: what AI actually thinks about your brand,
    the gaps most brands don't know they have, and the difference between owning
    the answer and owning the citation.
  </p>

  <h2>Recent</h2>
  <ul class="prose">
    <li><strong>Cincy AI Week</strong> — Featured Speaker. What AI actually thinks about your brand, and what to do about it.</li>
    <li><strong>Eastern Illinois University</strong> — guest lecture on AI visibility and modern marketing.</li>
    <li>Plus workshops and audit walk-throughs for brand and agency teams.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Topics I cover</h2>
  <ul class="prose">
    <li>How to audit your AI visibility, step by step</li>
    <li>Why your AI visibility "score" isn't the whole story</li>
    <li>The LinkedIn / newsletter pivot for getting cited by AI</li>
    <li>The lo-fi / analog pendulum swing and what it means for marketers</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3)">
    <a class="button" href={CTA.calendly}>Invite me to speak</a>
  </p>
</PageLayout>
